American axe
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:A double-edged axe, a double-bitted (or poss. a broad-bladed) axe
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: one with two cutting edges on the blade (??broad-bladed axe often called broad-axe and used spec. for splitting and shaping logs for e.g. sleepers). Also yankee axe, American.
